__**Special Containment Procedures:**__ While SCP-7057 has been declassified and hence does not require any containment procedures, Site-549 personnel should monitor civilian interactions with SCP-7057 and ensure their anomalous genetics are not discovered. SCP-7057's backstory and relevant documentation have been created and any discrepancies found in said documents should be reported to Site-549 director Hugh Bradley immediately. SCP-7057's identity should be protected in accordance with the Ethics Committee to ensure Foundation personnel interact with them naturally within a public setting. Any prior procedures for SCP-7057 have been discontinued.
----
__**Description:**__ //##grey|SCP-7057 is a humanoid possessing anomalous DNA which contains 2 additional base pairs, labelled Sermothine (S) and Yatromine (Y). It is believed that SCP-7057 is an individual from a similar yet slightly different reality from our own, the leading explanation for their unique genetics. SCP-7057 also has an inability to produce basic communication, however can comprehend basic speech from other individuals. SCP-7057 is confirmed to not possess reality-bending capabilities, maintaining a level of 1 Hume throughout many tests (See **Addendum #1**).##//

SCP-7057 was declassified as part of the [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6296 EVERSOR Initiative] and due to their apparent lack of any anomalous properties, save for their DNA and inexplicable origin. It was apparent to Site-549 personnel that containment of SCP-7057 was unnecessary and hence a declassification process for SCP-7057 begun.

__NOTE:__ No further connection between [[[SCP-7805]]] and SCP-7057 has been documented up to the time of declassification of anomaly (6/12/2022).
----
