= __**Addendum #4 - Discussion regarding the declassification of SCP-7057**__
[[div class="email"]]
[[div class="tofrom"]]
**To:** Specialist Jayden Harman //(Site-01 Liaison)//
**From:** Dir. Bradley //(Head of Site-549)//
**Subject:** Request for the declassification of SCP-7057
**Attachment:** **##grey|SCP-7057 Declassification Plan##**
##grey|Sent: 23/11/2022, 12:35##
[[/div]]
------
Good afternoon, Specialist Harman.

We at Site-549 have been following your advice on which low-level anomalies we should be neutralizing very closely. However, we think it would set a bad precedent if we were to neutralize SCP-7057. Hence, I propose that due to 7057 apparently not having any notable anomalous properties that we should instead declassify them and send them back into the world.

Attached is a document outlining the steps we would take to ensure a smooth transition from anomaly to citizen, which I believe will still keep us above the line, economically speaking. Anyways, thanks for your guidance so far and hope you consider this option.

- Director Hugh Bradley

//**Staff of the SCP Foundation**//
//##grey|Head of Site 549##//
[[/div]]
[[div class="email"]]
[[div class="tofrom"]]
**To:** Dir. Bradley //(Head of Site-549)//
**From:** Specialist Jayden Harman //(Site-01 Liaison)//
**Subject:** RE:Request for the declassification of SCP-7057
##grey|Sent: 25/11/2022, 15:18##
[[/div]]
------
Director Bradley,

I have brought up your issue to the Decommissioning Department and while they believe it is ideal that anomalies are neutralized in most protocol pertaining to the EVERSOR Initiative, resources to successfully declassify SCP-7057 are likely to be scarce and will still end up decreasing monetary strain at Site-549. Hence, declassifying SCP-7057 seems like a viable option.

Should this action backfire and cost the Foundation more than originally planned, then I am afraid it may lead to the termination of your position as Head of Site-549. I hope you don't let us down.

Regards,
@@ @@Specialist Jayden Harman

//**Staff of the SCP Foundation**//
//##grey|Site-01 Liaison##//
